dc_description_s: United States. Army Map Service. North Decimal Degree 40.0000. South Decimal Degree 39.0000. East Decimal Degree -9.0000. West Decimal Degree -10.0000. Alternate title: Caldas Da Rainha, Portugal: Estremadura Province. Polyconic projection. With Portuguese-English glossary. Relief shown by 100 m. contour interval, gradient tint and spot heights. Standard map series designation: A.M.S. M581. "Compiled from Portugal, 1:50,000, Instituto Geografico, 1901, 32; 1:100,000, Instituto Geografico, sheet 22, 1937; 1:100,000, Servicos Geodesicos, 1865-71; 1:250,000, Estador Maior do Exercito, 1936-37; Road Map of Spain and Portugal, 1:400,000, A.M.S., sheet 46, Third Edition, 1943; Railways of Spain and Portugal 1:1,500,000, G.S.G.S. 1941, corrected from Intelligence Reports, 1942-44. Partially revised from aerial photography, 1942.".
dc_title_s: Iberian Peninsula 1:250,000: Caldas Da Rainha, sheet 46. Series A.M.S. M581
